<div id="banner">
	<h1>It doesn&#8217;t seem like there&#8217;s</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>It doesn&#8217;t seem like there&#8217;s any way to get weblogs that don&#8217;t have RSS into Radio&#8217;s system/pages/news section. I&#8217;ve got an idea for a little script that does this. It&#8217;ll be an RSS feed that returns a link to the webpage with a checksum as its description. When the page changes, the checksum will change, and Radio will think it&#8217;s a new item and add a link to its News page.</p>

<p class="posted">posted January 13, 2002 08:33 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_"></a>)  <a href="000088" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

